<HEAD>Celebrities Wait Tables In Fundraiser</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Brooke Shields and other
celebrities bussed tables and hawked their wares to raise money for
Dreammakers Inc., an organization that grants the wishes of
terminally ill children.
   Country musicians Lynn Anderson, Lee Greenwood and Charlie
Daniels joined local television news anchors and Shields to raise
an estimated $52,000 for the charity Wednesday.
   Gov. Ned McWherter and Mayor Bill Boner also joined in the Fifth
Annual Celebrity Waiters Luncheon.
