decorated with the Dreammakers logo to their fellows. Members of
the country music band Sawyer Brown bought Shields' apron for $500,
outbidding Davidson County Sheriff Fate Thomas and musician Chet
Atkins.
   The organization was created by Nancy West, who was presented
with the annual Dreammakers Award. She said the group's success
cannot be attributed to any one person.
   ``Let us not forget that this is the children who this is for
and I accept it on their behalf,'' she said.
