<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Group to Push for Palestinian State as Issue on Democratic, GOP
Platforms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Arab American Institute has launched a
national campaign to put the issue of a Palestinian state directly
in platforms of both political parties this summer.
   ``Every state that has a convention or caucus process we will be
there,`` said James Zogby, the advocacy group's executive director.
``And we will build a Middle East Peace Caucus in each convention
that will support this resolution.''
   Zogby explained that the campaign began as a trial program in
Iowa, Texas and California. In California the group intends to
introduce the resolution with petitions at the state's Democratic
convention this weekend.
   ``We chose the political system because we felt that's where
issues get debated and that's where one begins to influence the
shape and direction of policy in the '88 elections,'' he said.
   The three-year old institute, a planning and organizing center
for electoral strategies for the Arab-American community, already
has published a report on the presidential candidates' positions on
the Middle East.
</TEXT>
