<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0478</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Falls From Texas To New York; Cold Snap Continues In South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell today from Texas to New York state, while a cold snap
sent temperatures to record lows in Florida and prompted frost and
freeze warnings in South Carolina.
   Key West, Fla., recorded a low this morning of 53 degrees, tying
the record for the date set in 1901.
   Forecasters posted snow advisories for eastern Colorado,
northeast New Mexico, the northern Texas panhandle, northern Texas,
south-central Nebraska and parts of Missouri.
   The storm left as much as 6 inches at Goodland, Kan.; 3 inches
at Imperial, Neb.; 4 inches at Osborne, Kan.; 2 to 4 inches across
central Kansas; and 4 to 5 inches at Canadian, Texas.
   Snowfall during the 6 hours ending at 1 a.m. EST included 4
inches at Amarillo, Texas; 2 inches at Concordia and Topeka, Kan.;
and 1 inch at Casper, Wyo., Dodge City and Wichita, Kan., and
Pittsburgh.
   Snow continued into the morning across southwest New York state,
northern and western Pennsylvania, West Virginia and Ohio. Snow
also extended from northwest Missouri across Nebraska, Kansas,
northwest Oklahoma, the northern portion of the Texas panhandle,
northern New Mexico, Colorado and southern Wyoming.
   Rain fell from central and southwest Oklahoma into north-central
Texas.
   Today's forecast called for snow from the central Plains to the
middle Mississippi Valley. Rain and thunderstorms will reach from
the lower Mississippi Valley across eastern Texas. Highs will be in
the 30s from the northern and central Plains to northern New
England. Highs will generally reach the 50s and 60s west of the
Rockies, with 70s in Southern California. Highs also will reach the
50s and 60s from southern and central New Mexico across Louisiana
and southern Arkansas to the southern and middle Atlantic Coast,
with 70s over the lower Rio Grande Valley of Texas.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 1
degree above zero at Yellowstone, Wyo., to 67 degrees at
Brownsville, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 33 fair; Boston 32 fair; Buffalo 25 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 35 fair; Cincinnati 28 cloudy; Cleveland 30
cloudy; Detroit 25 partly cloudy; Miami 56 fair; New York 35 fair;
Philadelphia 35 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 24 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine 29 fair; Washington 34 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 11 fair; Chicago 31 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 52 cloudy; Denver 16 snow; Des Moines 27 snow;
Indianapolis 29 cloudy; Kansas City 32 snow; Minneapolis-St. Paul
30 cloudy; Nashville 28 fair; New Orleans 41 fair; St. Louis 30
fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 34 partly cloudy; Anchorage 27 snow; Las
Vegas 47 fair; Los Angeles 52 fair; Phoenix 56 fair; Salt Lake City
29 fair; San Diego 52 fair; San Francisco 47 fair; Seattle 44 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 21 fair; Toronto 21 fair.
</TEXT>
