<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-MustafaArafat     03-17 0181</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Mustafa Arafat,0186</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Older Brother Of PLO Leader Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A brother of PLO chairman Yasser Arafat died
today in a Cairo hospital after a long bout with liver cancer, a
third Arafat brother said.
   Mustafa Arafat, 62, died at the Palestinian Red Crescent
Hospital, said Fat'hy Arafat, who is the hospital's director.
   Mustafa Arafat, who was manager of the Palestine Automobile Club
in Cairo, is survived by his wife. His funeral will be held in
Cairo on Friday.
   Both Fat'hy Arafat and spokesman Ahmed Abdul-Rahman at Palestine
Liberation Organization headquarters in Tunis said they did not
know whether the 57-year-old PLO leader will attend the funeral.
   Mustafa Arafat was born in Jerusalem and went to school there
and in Cairo. He was in private business until the early 1960s,
when he joined Fatah, the largest of eight factions that make up
the PLO.
   Yasser Arafat founded Fatah and officially launched it in 1965.
   The Arafat brothers also have a sister living in Cairo. She is
known by her code-name Um al-Mumeneen, or ``Mother of the
Faithful.''
