   The Pentagon said the four battalions would be assembled into an
infantry brigade task force under the command of Army Brig. Gen.
Daniel R. Schroeder, the chief of staff of the XVIII Airborne Corps
at Fort Bragg.
   The battalions will conduct field exercises with Honduran units
after arriving today and Friday, the Pentagon said. The battalions
are carrying three OH-58 observation helicopters; four AH-1 Cobra
attack helicopters; 1 UH-60 utility transport copter, and 2 M-551
Sheridan light tanks, the Pentagon added.
   The Pentagon identified the individual units involved in the
deployment as:
