<HEAD>Bus Falls in River; 27 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus traveling a winding mountain road
through heavy rain and fog plunged into a river on Thursday,
killing 27 people and injuring four, the Sao Paulo State Highway
Department said.
   The bus was carrying at least 31 people when it fell into the
shallow, muddy Casqueiro River in southeastern Brazil near the port
city of Santos, about 45 miles from Sao Paulo, said Nilton de
Carvalho, the department's operations director.
   He said 27 bodies were recovered, and 19 were identified. Of the
four survivors, two were hospitalized in critical condition,
Carvalho said.
   Buses that cover the Sao Paulo-Santos route normally pick up
other passengers along the way, so there may be more dead.
   Carvalho said the bus was on the river bed ``with its wheels
sticking out of the water.''
   The cause of the accident was unknwon.
