<HEAD>Former U.S. News Correspondent Dead at 67</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John P. ``Jack'' Sutherland, former White
House correspondent for U.S. News and World Report, is dead at age
67.
   Sutherland, 67, died Wednesday of a heart attack at his home in
suburban Alexandria, Va. He had reported on the U.S. presidency
from Harry S Truman through Gerald Ford's administration. He then
became associate editor of the U.S. News Washington Letter, the
post he held when he retired in 1985.
