<HEAD>Regan Book to be Out May 16</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The publication date of a book by former White
House chief of staff Donald T. Regan has been moved to May based
``on the revelations and scope'' of the manuscript, it was
announced Thursday.
   Harcourt Brace Jovanovich said in a statement that Regan
delivered the manuscript of ``For the Record: From Wall Street to
Washington,'' last week and it would be in stores by May 16.
   The book ``offers fresh insight into the dynamics of the Reagan
White House, including revelations concerning the unorthodox
factors that influence the decision-making process,'' the statement
said.
   The book had been scheduled to come out in September. Harcourt
Brace Jovanovich paid $1 million for the publishing rights.
