<HEAD>Jobless Rate Falls to 9.1 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Britain fell to a seasonally
adjusted 9.1 percent of the work force in February from 9.2 percent
in January, the government said Thursday.
   The figure was down from 11 percent in February 1987, the
Department of Employment said.
   Seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 2.53 million
people in February, down from a revised 2.56 million people in
January and 3.07 million people in February 1987.
