<1ST_LINE>u f BC-OPEC     03-17 0207</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-OPEC,0214</2ND_LINE>
<BYLINE>OPEC President To Call Press Conference On Oil Prices</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   OPEC President Rilwanu Lukman said
Thursday he will announce new measures to bring stability to
dropping oil prices on March 22.
   Lukman's two-paragraph statement did not say what the measures
would involve. The statement said the measures would be announced
at a 10:00 a.m. (4 a.m. EST) press conference and should bring
stability to the volatile oil market.
   On Tuesday, Lukman accused the Western press of trying to
destabilize the oil market to bring down prices. He said OPEC would
not be stampeded into taking emergency measures to stop the fall of
oil prices.
   He said the cartel would stand firm on its decision to produce
15.6 million barrels of oil a day. A barrel is the equivalent of 42
gallons.
   Ministry sources, who declined to be identified, said Lukman
would call an emergency OPEC meeting soon after the March 22 press
conference if consultations between members promised meaningful
discussion at the meeting.
   The sources said price stability would be the main topic of
discussion if the meeting were held. A report by a private audit
team on the level of oil production among cartel members would also
be an issue.
</TEXT>
