<HEAD>Heinz Buys African Soap Maker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   H.J. Heinz Co. said Wednesday it acquired the
lone producer of toilet and laundry soap in the African nation of
Botswana.
   Kgalagadi Soap Industries of Gaborone, Botswana, which Heinz got
from Overseas Development Enterprises Ltd., operates a
33,000-square-foot facility that makes soap in various forms,
including cakes, bars, pieces and pellets.
