<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Retail,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>May Department Stores Reports Record Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Co. said Wednesday its
earnings rose 8 percent in the fourth quarter and 16.5 percent for
1987 as a whole.
   May, the nation's seventh-largest retailer, reported earnings of
$230 million, or $1.52 a share, in the quarter ended Jan. 31,
compared with earnings of $213 million, or $1.38 a share, during
the same period a year earlier.
   Sales for the latest quarter totaled $3.34 billion, up from $3.1
billion during the final quarter of fiscal 1986.
   For all of 1987, earnings totaled $444 million, or $2.90 a
share, up from $381 million, or $2.44 a share, in fiscal 1986.
   Sales totaled $10.31 billion for the year, up from $9.5 billion
in the previous year.
   May operates 2,960 department, discount and specialty stores.
Its divisions include Lord & Taylor and May department stores,
Venture and Caldor discount stores and Volume shoe stores.
   May president Thomas A. Hays said the company plans to open
seven department stores, seven discount stores and about 240
specialty stores in 1988.
